  "summary": "Colin Lamb visits a residence to return a silver-white fruit knife he found after it was dropped out of a window. He is met by Ingrid, a tall, blonde Norwegian woman who is currently cooking and has limited English proficiency. Ingrid leads Lamb to a living room where he meets Geraldine Mary Alexandrina Brown, a highly intelligent nine or ten-year-old girl with a plaster cast on her leg.\n\nDuring their conversation, Geraldine reveals that her father works at the Cattin's Mill Filament Factory in Harebridge and that her mother died in a plane crash when Geraldine was an infant. She explains that Ingrid has lived with them for two weeks and is teaching Geraldine Norwegian. Geraldine describes her habit of watching the neighborhood through a high-quality telescope, which she uses to observe neighbors and record details in a notebook. She assigns nicknames to the residents, such as \"the Countess Kalarabas\" for a woman living in a house with messy trees.\n\nGeraldine explains that her leg injury occurred when she was nearly run over by a bus. She also mentions that the house next door is occupied by a blind woman. The conversation turns serious when Geraldine reveals that the caretaker, Harry, told her about a murder case in that house. Geraldine claims she witnessed the aftermath of the event, noting that she heard a scream and saw someone run out of the house, which signaled that something had happened.",
